				<!-- start pageDataHeading -->
				<h1>Refundable Accommodation Deposit (RAD)/Daily Accommodation Payment (DAP) financial hardship assistance for aged care services  065-21050354</h1>
<ul id="tabs-primary"><li><a class="active students" href="../older-australians/065-21050354-01.html">Background</a></li><li><a href="../older-australians/065-21050354-03.html">Process</a></li><li><a href="../older-australians/065-21050354-05.html">Resources</a></li></ul>
				<!-- end pageDataHeading -->

				<!-- start pageDataContent -->
				<div id="bgtab" class="">
					
<div id="relatedMessagesDiv"></div>


					<div class="unitRight"><a href="javascript:expandCollapseSections()" id="toggleText" alt="Expand/Collapse all sections" title="Expand/Collapse all sections"><img src="../../supportingContent/images/icons/toggle_plus.gif"align="top" id="toggleImage"border="0" alt="Expand/Collapse all sections"width="16" height="16">Expand all</a></div><br><br>

					<body>
<a name="top" class="anchor"></a><div id="contentObp" class="main"><div id="topnav"></div>


<p>This document outlines information about the Refundable Accommodation Deposit (RAD)/Daily Accommodation Payment (DAP) financial hardship assistance. This includes historical processing in the System for Payment of Aged Residential Care (SPARC). This process is only applicable for care recipients who have entered into permanent residential care from 1 July 2014 and care recipients who have opted into the post 1 July 2014 means assessment arrangements.</p>

<p></p>
<div class="twisty">
	
<a class="anchor" name="bp01_L2GT_Historical_SPAR"></a>
<h2 id="bp01_L2GT_Historical_SPAR">Historical SPARC process</h2>

	<div class="collapsible_container">
		<div class="block">

<p>The System for the Payment of Aged Residential Care (SPARC) is the legacy aged care payment system for residential care. SPARC is a view only system from 11 August 2022. </p>

<p>To view the legacy SPARC process, see the <a href="../older-australians/065-21050354-01.html?PageVersion=3072">historical version</a>.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>


<p></p>
<div class="twisty">
	
<a class="anchor" name="bp01_L2GT_Refundable_Acco"></a>
<h2 id="bp01_L2GT_Refundable_Acco">Refundable Accommodation Deposit (RAD)/Daily Accommodation Payment (DAP)</h2>

	<div class="collapsible_container">
		<div class="block">

<p>Accommodation payments and contributions are payable by&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
all permanent residential care recipients who entered into care from 1 July 2014, and</li>
		<li>
care recipients who have opted into the post 1 July 2014 means assessment arrangements</li>
		</ul>
<p></p>

<p>The Refundable Accommodation Deposit (RAD)/Daily Accommodation Payment (DAP) financial hardship assistance is available for care recipients who&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
have been assessed with a resident status of not low means on the date of entry into permanent residential care, and</li>
		<li>
who are experiencing, or would experience financial hardship as a result of paying accommodation payments</li>
		</ul>
<p></p>

<p>The RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance is an additional supplement, which is paid to the aged care service with the service’s monthly claims. The RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance amount is equal to the amount the care recipient’s fees are reduced by and cannot exceed the maximum fee that would have been payable. The RAD/DAP is not applicable to care recipients who are assessed under the pre 1 July 2014 means assessment arrangements.</p>

<p>When care recipients are entitled to the RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance, the fees and/or accommodation payments can be reduced to any amount including setting the fees to zero. The reduction is dependent on the care recipient’s financial circumstances. The RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance can be granted for up to 3 years after Services Australia receives the RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance application. Care recipients must submit a new request with updated evidence to reapply for the RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance.</p>

<p>Due to a system limitation, SPARC was unable to automatically pay the RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance for care recipients who entered into a permanent residential care service from 1 July 2014. Manual intervention was required to ensure the RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance had been applied correctly. </p>

<p><strong>Historical RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance process</strong></p>
		<ul>		<li>
Prior to 1 August 2022, RAD/DAP hardship was&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
unable to be coded in SPARC</li>
			<li>
payments were made by a monthly manual adjustment</li>
			<li>
maintained manually via a spreadsheet</li>
			</ul>			</ul>
<p></p>

<p><strong>Current RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance process </strong></p>
		<ul>		<li>
From 1 August 2022, RAD/DAP hardship is&#58;</li>
			<ul>			<li>
coded in the Aged Care Staff Portal (ACSP)</li>
			<li>
coded from the start date</li>
			<li>
is an automatic payment from 1 August 2022 onwards</li>		</ul>
		<li>
paid as a manual adjustment for any period prior to 1 August 2022</li>
		<li>
includes care recipients with existing and new RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance</li>
		</ul>
<p></p>

<p>Service Officers must check to ensure the relevant care recipient is eligible for RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance prior to coding RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance in the Aged Care Staff Portal (ACSP). </p>

<p>The aged care system validates when a care recipient is not eligible for RAD/DAP financial hardship assistance when a care recipient&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
has been assessed with a resident status of low means</li>
		<li>
chooses not to have their means assessed and is deemed as means not disclosed (MND), or</li>
		<li>
has not completed a means assessment</li>
		</ul>
<p></p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>


<p>The <a href="../older-australians/065-21050354-05.html">Resources</a> page contains links to useful contact details and external websites.</p>

